$ NastAero VM1: Axial Rod Under Tension
$ Reference: Nastran Verification Manual Problem 1
$ A single rod (CBAR used as rod) under axial tension
$ L=10 in, A=1 in^2, E=30e6 psi, F=1000 lb
$ Analytical: delta = PL/AE = 1000*10/(1*30e6) = 3.333e-4 in
$ Stress = P/A = 1000 psi
$
SOL 101
CEND
TITLE = VM1 - AXIAL ROD UNDER TENSION
SPC = 1
LOAD = 1
DISPLACEMENT(PRINT) = ALL
SPCFORCES(PRINT) = ALL
BEGIN BULK
$
GRID,1,,0.0,0.0,0.0
GRID,2,,10.0,0.0,0.0
$
$ CBAR as axial rod
CBAR,1,1,1,2,0.0,1.0,0.0
$
$ A=1.0, I1=I2=0.0833 (dummy for bending), J=0.1406
PBAR,1,1,1.0,0.0833,0.0833,0.1406
MAT1,1,30.0e6,,0.3,0.0
$
$ Fix left end fully
SPC1,1,123456,1
$ Allow only X-translation at right end
SPC1,1,23456,2
$
$ Axial force in +X direction at node 2
FORCE,1,2,,1000.0,1.0,0.0,0.0
$
ENDDATA
